Description: Freshly roasted ground coffee beans percolated to perfection and mixed with an equal amount of thick dairy cream. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Triple Cream Coffee

Description: Soft dough mixed with thick-sliced bacon and twisted into a pattern resembling a sheaf of wheat. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Bacon Bread

Description: Salted eggs of the rare emperor fish. Often referred to as black diamonds, the eggs are a delicacy that can only be afforded by the wealthiest of connoisseurs. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Flint Caviar

Description: The massive fin of a megalodon, boiled in a rich Far Eastern broth until soft and gelatinous. While not included in the soup, the remainder of the sharkflesh is salted and dried until rock hard, then shaved into paper-thin slices which, when boiled in hot water, create a savory soup that is the base of countless other recipes. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Shark Fin Soup

Description: A thick salty dip made from a purée of haddock, raw egg, and mashed popotoes. A favorite of Roegadyn tribes hailing from the north seas. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Haddock Dip

Description: Though technically a soup, this Ixali dish consists mainly of large slabs of smoked bacon boiled with several other lesser ingredients. EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Bacon Broth

Description:
A fraction of the size, yet every bit as annoying as the real thing. Be forewarned: once Ultros shows up, he's liable to stick around.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ultros minion.
Name: Wind-up Ultros

Description:
Hoary the Snowman was a jolly happy soul, without a pipe, and without a nose, and two eyes made out of something other than coal. Probably slag.

Use item to acquire the Hoary the Snowman minion.
Name: Hoary the Snowman

Description:
Currently, “baby fat” is the prevailing excuse for this cherubic chick's gigant-like girth.

Use item to acquire the heavy hatchling minion.
Name: Heavy Hatchling

Description:
Despite convincing research by top academics from around the realm and beyond, most Miqo'te scholars refuse to believe that there may be some ancestral connection between their race and cats (fat or not).

Use item to acquire the fat cat minion.
Name: Fat Cat

Description:
This particular yeti is content in knowing that bigger is not always necessarily better.

Use item to acquire the Littlefoot minion.
Name: Littlefoot

Description:
While as cute as a button, remember, mummies are ultimately embalmed corpses damned to eternal thralldom in the land of the living. Have fun.

Use item to acquire the mummy's little mummy minion.
Name: Mummy's Little Mummy

Description:
There was an old betta who swallowed a fry. No one knows why it swallowed the fry, but for some reason, the fry can now fly.

Use item to acquire the assassin fry minion.
Name: Assassin Fry

Description:
Legend states these strange creatures can only survive on land as long as the plate atop their heads remains wet.

Use item to acquire the water imp minion.
Name: Water Imp

Description:
The Seventh Astral Era is secure as long as the Archon is ever at our sides.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Louisoix minion.
Name: Wind-up Louisoix

Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your parade chocobo.
Name: Parade Chocobo Whistle

Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon Boreas, the steed of legend.
Name: Boreas Whistle

Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Lady of Frost, Shiva.
Name: Ice Barding

Description: A powerful adhesive developed and used by the Ehcatl Nine.
Name: Quick-hardening Sealant

Description: Slightly effervescent water bottled at a spring located deep in the heart of the Ixali homeland, Xelphatol. It has a light-blue tint and a distinctly metallic flavor.
Name: Xelphatol Spring Water

Description: An ingot of smelted wootz alloy.
Name: Wootz Ingot

Description: A small nugget of impure platinum.
Name: Platinum Nugget

Description: An ingot of smelted platinum.
Name: Platinum Ingot

Description: A large piece of cured skin from the chimerical monstrosity Kirimu.
Name: Kirimu Leather

Description: Thick cloth woven from the web of the chimerical monstrosity Arachne.
Name: Arachne Velveteen

Description: A small chunk of the alloy used by the Allagan Empire to craft heavy armor.
Name: Allagan Wootz Nugget

Description: A large piece of treated chimerical leather used by the Allagan Empire to craft light armor.
Name: Allagan Leather

Description: A spool of thick chimerical silk used by the Allagan Empire to craft mage robes.
Name: Allagan Silk

Description: This soft lusterless crystal is believed to stay the hands of corruption and is used in the preservation of organics.
Name: Borax

Description: The wire-like web of the Allagan chimerical miscreation, Arachne.
Name: Arachne Web

Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing naturally occurring wootz alloy.
Name: Wootz Ore

Description: Developed by a Far Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to harden platinum.
Name: Raziqsap

Description: A greasy mixture of wax, oil, and tallow used for waterproofing and softening leather, while helping maintain its luster.
Name: Dubbin

Description: A large side of boar, cured and then smoked. It is widely accepted across Eorzea that “everything goes better” with this flavorful meat.
Name: Smoked Bacon

Description: Seeds harvested from the coffee plants which grow in volcanic mountainous soils, and then slow-roasted over an indirect flame for several bells to remove bitterness and bring out flavor.
Name: Roasted Coffee Beans

Description: Ink fortified with platinum sand to improve aetherial conductivity.
Name: Enchanted Platinum Ink

Description: A pair of blood-soaked blades retrieved from the site of a gruesome battle.
Name: Bloody Knife Blades

Description: A pair of daggers crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. They are so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.
Name: Mossy Stone Daggers

Description: Dubbed a “god in the machina” by those who first discovered it, modern scholars have yet to discover not only what the catalytic agent contains, but exactly how it functions, understanding only that the substance is required to strengthen the properties of certain materials.
Name: Allagan Catalyst

Description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost.
Name: Ice Tear

Description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost. It pulses with uncontrollably powerful ice-aspected energies.
Name: Diamond Tear

Description: A remarkably transparent piece of Syrcus Tower's outer wall.
Name: Syrcus Shard

Description: A crystallized fragment of the dreadwyrm Bahamut's burning heart.
Name: Burning Auricle

Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.
Name: Rowena's Token (Poetics)

Description: While Garlond Ironworks engineers insist tomestones contain reams of invaluable information gathered by the lost Allagan Empire, even they are at a loss how to decipher the content of this particular one. This variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.
Name: Encrypted Tomestone

Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemical concoction is said to increase a gem's hardness. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Carboncoat

Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemically engineered fiber can be used to improve the durability of almost anything. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Carbontwine

Description: Collectors were once known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered these worthless.
Name: Antique Tassets

Description: Deadly darksteel blades used in the creation of misericordes.
Name: Misericorde Blades
